				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} y = \frac{a}{1+ e^{-c(x-d)}} + b \end{aligned}$$\end{document}y=a1+e-c(x-d)+bHere, x represents the total number of confirmed cases till 12th July 2020 and y represents the closest value fitted to the actual value based on the logistic function. Parameter a represents the value that can be reached on the basis of the fit; b defines the vertical shift from the axis; c defines the slope of the curve; d defines the horizontal shift from the axis. The initial guess values are defined as : a=1, b=0, c=1, d=0. Fitting up these values in Eq. (1), yields the equation of the most basic logistic curve :2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
