				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} y = \frac{a}{1+ e^{-x}} + b \end{aligned}$$\end{document}y=a1+e-x+bStarting from this initial guess, parameter values are estimated for the four different state cases. This estimation is based on the curve fitting to the data set. The estimated parameter values are shown in Table 2.

The time step is one, i.e. each incremental day’s data is taken into consideration. Based upon the function, the curve fitting for the actual and the predicted models is shown in Fig. 1, along with their \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
