				\begin{document}$$R^{2}$$\end{document}R2 value for each fitted model. From the plot of Covid-19 data in Fig. 1 (where observations are the actual data points), it is visible that the growth rate of the infection is nonlinear. Further, fitting the data points using a logistic regression-based model brings us to the conclusion that the growth rate is exponential. The argument is justified based on the value of the coefficient of determination (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
